content: Oh, my goodness. Camilla Cream loved lima beans, but she never ate them. All her friends hated lima beans, and she wanted to fit in. Camilla was always worried about what other people thought of her. Today, she was fretting even more than usual. It was the first day of school, and she couldn't decide what to wear. There were so many people to impress. She tried on forty-two outfits, but none seemed quite right. She put on a pretty red dress and looked in the mirror. Then, she screamed. Her mother ran into the room, and she screamed too. "Oh my heavens!" She cried. "You're completely covered with stripes!"

speaker: parent
content: This was certainly true. Camilla was striped from head to toe. She looked like a rainbow. Mrs. Cream felt Camilla's forehead. "Do you feel all right?" she asked. "I feel fine," Camilla answered, "but just look at me."

speaker: parent
content: "You get back into bed this instant!" Her mother ordered. You're not going to school today. Camilla was relieved. She didn't want to miss the first day of school, but she was afraid of what the other kids would say. And she had no idea what to wear with those crazy stripes.

speaker: parent
content: That afternoon, Dr. Bumble came to examine Camilla. "Most extraordinary!" He exclaimed. "I've never seen anything like it. Are you having any coughing, sneezing, runny nose, aches, pains, chills, hot flashes, dizziness, shortness of breath, or uncontrollable twitching?" "No," Camilla told him. "I feel fine."

speaker: parent
content: "Well then," said Dr. Bumble, turning to Mrs. [crosstalk 00:10:39]

speaker: parent
content: The next day was a disaster. Everyone at school laughed at Camilla. They called her "Camilla Crayon", and "Night of the Living Lollipop". She tried her best to act as everything were normal, but when the class said the Pledge of Allegiance, her stripes turned red, white, and blue, and she broke out in stars.

speaker: parent
content: The other kids thought this was great. One yelled out, "Let's see some purple polka dots!" Sure enough, Camilla turned all purple polka-dotty. Someone else shouted out, "Checkerboard!" And a pattern of squares covered her skin. Soon, everyone was calling out different shapes and colors, and pour Camilla was changing faster than you can change TV channels.

speaker: parent
content: That night, Mr. Harms, the school principal, called. "I'm sorry, Mrs. Cream," he said. "I'm going to have to ask you to keep Camilla home from school. She's just too much of a distraction. I've been getting calls from other parents. They're afraid...those stripes may be contagious."

speaker: parent
content: Camilla was so embarrassed. She couldn't believe that two days ago everyone liked her. Now, no one wanted to be in the same room as her. Her father tried to make her feel better. "Is there anything I can get you, sweetheart?" He asked.

content: "Hmm, well, yes. I see," Dr. Bumble mumbled when Mrs. Cream phoned the next day. "I think we'd better bring in the specialists. I'll be right over."

content: About an hour later, Dr. Bumble arrived with four people in long, white coats. He introduced them to the Cream's.
